eceived more help than should ever be asked of others to get to where I am.  I have had my share of great fortune and luck i.e. hate staff and aggravation beyond belief with camping Najena for two weeks for three pieces of paper and thirteen Phin raids to get the water staff.  Najena and Phin I have gotten to know so well they have offered me jobs working in their respective lairs since only the diehard visit there regularly.  We all have horror stories to tell about Quillamane and the many other insanely rare mobs and the rare drops off them we need.  <br>
<br>
I will like Elwynd be as much relieved as excited to complete my epic.  I have helped many others with epics and the frustration with watching the relative ease with which some can be completed is disheartening but in the end only makes ours that much more precious.  The only positive in comparison to other epics is we don't have to camp Ragefire.  I have given up the hope of actually raiding the PoA for the crown I need and will just have to earn the cash and belittle the effort so far put into the epic and purchase it if I can even find a seller.   I don't see VI making any major changes on our epic as we are slowly being phased out as a class with the revamp to wizzies and beastlords being a popular alternative if someone wants a pet class.  We are the few, the proud, the Mages!  I think we kick ass, don't give up on your epic the reward will be worth the effort. <p>Availin <BR>
59 Conjurer <BR>
